<br>
A major role of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>dealing damage</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should be a significant source of <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>dealing damage</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> engender great risk, and therefore should yield great rewards<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> do not scale well past 50.<br>
In particular, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are generally not welcome on raids, due both to the risk, and inadequate damage output against high end mobs.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Therefore, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pet Damage Output</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> should be increased post-50.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Several means exist to increase pet damage output, including:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Raising the raw level</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of post-50 pets slightly.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Increasing the raw statistics</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of post-50 pets, in particular attack, strength, dexterity, and AC.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Stronger pet buffs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> including <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or new pet buffs.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Summoned Pet Only Items</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that increase statistics or have procs.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AAXP Magician Class Skills</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that increase pet statistics or add procs.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Moving Pets to a new combat table</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that would increase pet damage output.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Raid Specific &quot;Bane&quot; Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that only work against specific types of endgame targets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Possible Arguments <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>against</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Increasing Pet Strength:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are already completely adequate as is, and need no improvements.<br>
Stronger pets may increase <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s infamous ability to gain <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
If <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chain Casting Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is over-powering, it would increase that ability.<br>
In so far as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are already desirable in groups, it would make them even more powerful.<br>
It would make <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> better soloers, which <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> wishes to discourage.<br>
It would not help on <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>raids</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, where <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Elementals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are already not allowed.<br>
The existance of an <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>adequate</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> second character is already over-powering, it would only increase that.<br>
<br>
In order to successfully increase pet power significantly, the arguments above must be refuted.<br>
<br>
I believe that several things limit what is possible or likely.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Chain Casting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> suggest that significant increases to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Raw Pet Power</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> are less likely.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dire Charm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician Epic Pet</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> likely represent an upper limit to pet damage output.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Stronger Pet Buffs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would have the advantage, from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s point of view, of being limited to effecting our own pets, and would not increase the utility of either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Pet Chaining</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AFK Experience</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Summoned Pet Only Items</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> could be given to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>other's</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> pets, which would increase their utility and foster inter-class dependencies.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AAXP Magician Class Skills</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are only available at level 59, and like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> leave our younger brethren out in the cold.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Raid Specific &quot;Bane&quot; Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would likely only be available at level 59+, likewise leaving junior <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> out in the cold.<br>
<br>
Despite my conclusion that increased pet power is at most necessary in the very endgame, I am happy to help organize a petition of this kind so that we will not find ourselves <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Short On Luck</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> when the developers move on to the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Legends Server</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I would be more than happy to a stronger advocate of this approach take the lead here, but I have seen no organized movement in that direction.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mage of a Thousand Words, and Abuser of EZCodes<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uonyxrosevalsharess.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OnyxroseValSharess</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 279<br> <font color=#333333>(2/4/02 8:51:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=82.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Increased Pet Strength, Summary Pro and Con</span><hr size=1> I do not disagree that pets need to have their abilities improved.  After playing in the 50's game for a while, I've seen what a properly equipped (melee) player can do, which then points out the lack of items that similarly improve caster abilities.<br>
<br>
The devil is in the details, or in this case, the delivery to the players.  Verant will not &quot;gift&quot; anyone with equipment, they have said as much in the past.  The key is, though we demand it, Magicians as a whole are not &quot;entitled&quot; to improvements.  Getting them to improve a class is like pulling teeth -- they will only listen to thousands of petitions.<br>
<br>
I feel we need to present (1) the case that pets need improvement, and (2) a method whereby players may &quot;upgrade&quot; themselves.  <br>
<br>
An equipped melee is powerful, yes.  But note that qualifier, equipped... that means they (or someone) had to go to a dungeon or high-level encounter and find that equipment.  Or, they had to gain experience to get the disciplines to become mighty.<br>
<br>
The caster community, on the other hand, feels slighted, because (1) we have no disciplines, (2) equipment that raises magic output (on the same scale as melee items) isn't in the game, and (3) items are so not in the game, they don't even exist in code yet.<br>
<br>
So, it is my opinion, that we need to present methods of improving the abilities of our class at a &quot;gradual&quot; level that is dependant on individuals.  The optimum, individualized &quot;deployment&quot; would be through either (1) new spells or (2) alternative advancements.  Spells are equivalent to dropped swords and armor, which become &quot;no drop&quot; when they are memorized.  AA skills are like disciplines, given when experience is accumulated over time. <br>
<br>
I would personally like more spells, found on high end mobs same as melee weaponry and armors.  And not like SoL spells, I mean at least 2 or 3 dozen new spells, of varying effect.<br>
<br>
New Spells, and Player Usage:<br>
-- Spell Drops, found on the dead in high encounters, some tradeable and some NO DROP<br>
-- Research Only Spells, requiring components found scattered accross the expansions<br>
-- Wands with Effects of said spells, found like weaponry<br>
<br>
I am currently against the Alternative Advancement method, because of the botched job of the current AA skill set.  Apparently, VI feels that players must be lvl 59 or 60 before they can enjoy any improvements in their class... well, that is just plain too late for 98% of the mage community.<br>
