own&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is also not as great as it seems.  I would rather focus on an <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>adequate</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> level of damage, enough to ensure that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;stack&quot; and are welcome on raids beyond the first two.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Goladus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Or, instead of a &quot;stronger&quot; pet buff, how about a &quot;raid/group&quot; pet buff that remains useful in the presence of an enchanter.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  I have some other ideas along these line.  However, I want to minimize the number of new spells that we propose, and there are other avenues which I will suggest later.  However, your idea has the virtue of promoting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;inter-class dependency,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and avoids the problems that you listed.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Goladus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  a dropped item proc<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  I am about to propose a specific proc for pet-only weapons that drop as loot.  These would be too expensive to use on ordinary soloing or grouping, and would only be used on raids in practice.  This would also allow <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to control the rate at which they entered the game.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Goladus:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  The use of new content...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->  I want to propose a small variety of incremental fixes that minimizes the amount of new content that is required.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Development Team</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is already busy with the new <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Legends Server</i><!--EZCODE 