iency is in damage dealt in the high end raid game.  Also, as levels rise, raiding generally assumes greater importance.  For many <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, raiding is the only arena in which they feel under powered.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WEZLOC:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  no guild leader is going to risk a pet causing the death of 40 people<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Which is why I support <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If I had to chose <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Stronger Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I would chose<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Indifferent Pets</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in a heartbeat.  In <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>59</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> levels, I have never found <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> inadequate to the task, either in groups or solo.  Other <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> also feel this way, and apparently <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> thinks pets are over-powered as it is.  Curse them as loudly as you like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (I know I do when the mood strikes me)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>they</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> are going to be the ones who make the decision, not us.  You have to convince <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>them</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, not me.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WEZLOC:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I dont agree that Verant wont do anything to help us solo better.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Let me be a bit more precise here.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has repeatedly stated that they wish to discourage soloing and encouraging grouping.  Because of this, they will generally look with a critical eye towards the impact of proposed changes on soloing.  Anything whose <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>sole</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> purpose is to improve soloing will not even be considered.<br>
